HEADWORD: Carpetmonger
<hw>Car"pet*mon`ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who deals in carpets; a buyer and seller of carpets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One fond of pleasure; a gallant.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

